sub_title: MSc student Bio inspired innovation | Biomimicry Enthusiast | Biologist | One for Interdisciplinary Collaboration | Looking for an Internship
summary:
With strong experience in biomimicry and biological research, I am able to define human problems, search for biological models, and translate biological knowledge into design strategies. I am looking forward to undertaking more projects and applying biomimicry to create a more sustainable and regenerative future! 

A great love of nature has led me to start a biomimicry journey and become a biomimicry enthusiast. I did my Bachelor's degree in Life Sciences at National Cheng Kung University in Taiwan. I presented biomimicry concepts to public audiences at the 2019 Life Sciences Department Exhibition at NCKU. Also, I formed an interdisciplinary team - RICOCHET, and worked on a biomimicry design from zero to one. We joined the 2020 Biomimicry Global Design Challenge and gained Finalist Achievement. Currently, I am studying in Bio Inspired Innovation Master's program at Utrecht University in the Netherlands.
